odysseus.common.entities

Class AbsLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • odysseus.common.entities.AbsLevel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Lightning, Puzzle, Release

    public abstract class AbsLevel
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A level is composed of a board, bullpen with pieces, and an objective for play. The level is serializable and save to disk. Meeting score requirements gains stars that are saved. Getting one star unlocks the next level. The first level is always unlocked. The Level class is used as an abstract model for the special level types.
    Author:
    Carlos Barcelos
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
